Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Unit 1315. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Walking round the monument to the on-the-spot guidance given by President Kim Il Sung, he was briefed on the history of the unit. He highly appreciated the great successes made by the servicepersons of the unit in the past through a dynamic drive to implement the on-the-spot instructions given by the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned about the unit's performance of duty before watching its servicepersons in training. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth important tasks which would serve as guidelines for further intensifying the combat training, a basic guarantee for increasing its combat capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He acquainted himself with the political work conducted among the servicepersons, going round a political lecture room, an educational room and other cultural and educational facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He praised the unit for having trained all its servicepersons as fighters of Ri Su Bok and Kang Ho Yong types in the era of Songun possessed of ardent patriotism by dynamically conducting the political work to suit their characteristic features. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Informed that the beautiful trait of the unity between the army and the people is being fully displayed at the unit, he underscored the need to take a lot of pictures of soldiers and people helping and leading each other forward to make these fine traits known. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He took deep care of the living of soldiers, making the rounds of a bedroom, a mess hall, a wash-cum-bath house, a kimchi store, a non-staple food store, a barn and other supply service facilities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was greatly satisfied to learn that the unit has provided its soldiers with rich diet by successfully doing sideline farming and stock breeding and other sideline job. This signal success is the fruition of the tenacious efforts made by the commanding officers and men of the unit in firm unity, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave the servicepersons of the unit a pair of binoculars, a machine gun and an automatic rifle as gifts and had a photo session with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

Establishment of Great Tradition of Devotedly Defending Leader 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- The Korean people extol anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk as a legendary general of lifeguard. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This designation implies her great feat in the establishment of the glorious tradition of defending the leader of the revolution at the cost of life, which is the pride and legacy of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She participated in the sacred war against Japanese imperialism in her early age. Convinced that the implementation of the Juche-oriented line of the Korean revolution advanced by President Kim Il Sung was precisely the way for the resurrection of the nation, she hardened her mind to dedicate her youth and life to the struggle for protecting the leader of the revolution with her very life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During the grim days of the anti-Japanese war, she, with a thorough-going thought that any slightest mistake should not be permitted in guarding the President, frustrated at every step the enemy's wicked scheme to hurt the revolutionary headquarters at camping sites and on march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She guarded the safety of the President with her body on the fierce battlefields including the battles at the entrance to Dashahe, Fusong County Seat and Hongqihe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She also regarded supporting the revolutionary idea of the President as the loftiest and honorable duty of the soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She resolutely struggled against the renegades of the revolution who were frightened by the enemy's bluff in the period of the most difficult trial during the anti-Japanese armed struggle and thus defended the purity of the revolutionary ideas of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She also set a brilliant example in thoroughly carrying out the revolutionary line and operational plan of the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She was often assigned important duties of political work from the President and conducted activities for awakening and organizing masses in vast areas and the homeland, making a special contribution to expanding the Association for the Restoration of the Fatherland, promoting the preparatory work for founding the Party and to maturing the all-people resistance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When she was given a task to make 600 suits of military uniform in a month, she, together with several sewing members, fulfilled the task with poor sewing tools only in 20 days. Like this, she devotedly carried out the orders given by the President, thus becoming the brilliant paragon to be followed by the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 She invariably paid special attention to protecting the safety of the President as a "bodyguard" in the years of building a new country and exerted her heart and soul to accomplish his nation-building line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Indeed, the noble feat performed by Kim Jong Suk to protect the fortune of the Korean people who were blessed with the illustrious leader President Kim Il Sung peerless in the 5,000-year-long history of the nation by devotedly defending him will shine for ever in the history of the fatherland.

Whole Life of Kim Jong Suk Devoted to Comrades and Revolution 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- The Korean people are recollecting with deep emotion the noble life of the anti- Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk with the approach of the 90th birth anniversary of the woman general of Mt. Paektu whose life was run through with revolutionary comradeship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Her philosophy of life was that it was happy to have other's affection, but still happier was to give it to others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@She had rare character and human touch. She intensely loved people and was ready to jump into water and fire, if it was for comrades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Cherishing it as her steadfast faith that her happiness and honor lay in devotedly defending President Kim Il Sung, she became a shield in guarding him in many battles such as the Fusong County Seat battle and the battle at the entrance to Dashahe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Deeply concerned for the health of the President, she, shivering with cold in winter, dried his wet clothes with the warmth of her body.  And she secured silk cotton and made a padded overcoat and knitted a waistband and woolen socks for him at odd moments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@In his reminiscences "With the Century" he recollects that she protected him from bullets, snow and rain, and chill with her own body. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@In the days of an arduous march, she mended torn clothes of comrades all night beside a campfire. When a battle was raging in Shuangshanzi in April Juche 27 (1938), she shared out food to the fighters by plunging into the battlefield after climbing a steep cliff, not to let them skip the meal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@When comrades-in arms had to eat potatoes only for several days, with rice running out in the unit, she, taking it close to heart, ground potatoes and made pancakes with them and made potato cakes, stuffing them with edible herbs which she had collected. All the fighters ate them deliciously. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Everything she did in the flames of the anti-Japanese struggle was not for herself, but for the President and for the comrades and the revolution.

Birth Anniversary of Kim Jong Suk Commemorated by Peasants 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- A meeting of agricultural workers and members of the Union of Agricultural Workers of Korea took place on December 20 to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting, Hong Jong Chol, vice-chairman of the Union Central Committee, said that all the agricultural workers and the members of the union should model after Kim Jong Suk, woman commander of Mt. Paektu, to faithfully uphold the idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il and work heart and soul to accomplish the cause of Songun revolution of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Ok Sun, an anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter, at the meeting recalled that Kim Jong Suk set a noble model of devotedly defending the leader and stressed that her precious exploits will shine generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Persons related to the revolutionary career of Kim Jong Suk took the floor to tell about the unforgettable stories about her visits to their working places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented at the meeting was female trio "Arirang on Jiansanfeng".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting said that the bright future of the country ardently desired by great revolutionary fighter Kim Jong Suk is being brought earlier by Kim Jong Il and expressed their firm determination to become genuine peasant heroes in the Songun era upholding his leadership with grain production.

Exhibition of Immortal Flowers Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- An exhibition of immortal flowers opened at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition Friday on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of the supreme commandership of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seen in the exhibition hall is a large mosaic depicting President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il standing together in a beautiful flower garden. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Models of the bright star of Marshal and the old home of Kim Jong Suk in Hoeryong are seen on the exhibition stand where potted Kimilsungias and Kimjongilias are in full bloom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Visitors are deeply impressed to see the beautiful flowers in full bloom in midwinter.

Foreign Diplomats Visit Pyongyang Cultural Exhibition 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- The corps of economic and commercial councilors here visited the Pyongyang Cultural Exhibition Friday on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They looked round photos and books dealing with the immortal exploits of the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the visit Commercial Councilor of the Cuban embassy Enrique Gomez Soler, who is doyen of the corps, wrote in the visitor's book that their visit to the exhibition helped them know better the great revolutionary exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and Kim Jong Suk, mother of Korea.

Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from Foreign Diplomats 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a congratulatory letter by the corps of economic and commercial councilors here on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was handed to an official concerned Friday by Commercial Councilor of the Cuban embassy Enrique Gomez Soler, doyen of the corps.

Foreign Diplomats Visit Revolutionary Museum  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- Diplomatic envoys of various countries and representatives of international organizations here visited the Revolutionary Museum of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces Friday on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The guests looked round historic relics on display. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They enjoyed a music and dance performance given by the Mansudae Art Troupe at the East Pyongyang Grand Theatre on the same day.

Meeting of Youth and Students Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- A meeting of youth and students took place at the Central Youth Hall on December 20 to celebrate the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Myong Won, secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, made a report which was followed by speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers said it is a great fortune of Kim Il Sung's nation that it has had Kim Jong Il at the top post of the revolutionary armed forces. They said that it is a historic event of weighty significance in defending and successfully accomplishing the cause of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His assumption of the KPA supreme commandership made it possible for the army and people of the DPRK to reliably carry forward the tradition of army of Mt. Paektu and greet the new glorious era of Songun revolution, they noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that every trace of his Songun leadership is associated with deep love and trust with which he has pursued the policy of attaching great importance to the youth as well as the policy of giving importance to the army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called upon all the youths to further increase the national defence capability and take the lead in every important project for building an economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recited at the meeting was celebration poem "Glory to General Kim Jong Il, Songun illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu."

Visa Free Agreement Signed between DPRK and Belarus
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Moscow, December 19 (KCNA) -- An agreement on exempting visa for diplomatic and official passport bearers between the governments of the DPRK and Belarus was signed in Moscow on December 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the signing ceremony from the DPRK side were Kim Yong Jae, DPRK ambassador to Russia, and staff members of the embassy and from the Belarusian side Vasili Dolgolev, Belorusian ambassador to Russia, and staff members of the embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The agreement was inked by Kim Yong Jae and Dolgolev.

Writings by Foreign Students in DPRK Presented
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- A meeting "Song devoted to December" to present the writings done by foreign students studying at Kim Il Sung University and Kim Hyong Jik University of Education took place at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on December 20 on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting started with chorus "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il", performers put on the stage numbers they prepared with boundless reverence for the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They successfully presented the ardent reverence for Kim Jong Il and strong yearning for Kim Jong Suk through diary "Invincible Strong Army", impressions "DPRK which I Have Seen", note "My First University", poem "Mother of Korea", travelogue "Visit to Kim Jong Suk Nursery" and other stories of diverse genres. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They highly eulogized the personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man and the indomitable fighting spirit and great exploits of Kim Jong Suk in the numbers including male chorus "The General Is the Son of Guerillas", piano solo "Kim Jong Suk Is Our Mother" and female chorus "Arirang on Jiansanfeng".

Centenarians Increase in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- Centenarians are increasing in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year alone, eight people greeted their 100th birthdays. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them there are Kim Pu Yong residing in Tongmyong-dong, Rason City, Choe Kil Bok in Jangbaek-dong, Munchon City, Kangwon Province, and Yo Sam Son in Kumhak-ri, Chongdan County, South Hwanghae Province, all women. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The centenarians are living an optimistic life, not letting their hands be idle after they were listed as pensioners. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They do not have an unbalanced diet. They like edible herbs, soy bean, vegetables, sea-foods, kimchi and bean paste soup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Grandma Choe Pu Yong residing in Samsong-ri, Samsok District, Pyongyang greeted her 110th birthday this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are dozens of other centenarians. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il sent birthday tables to all the centenarians greeting their 110th or 100th birthdays.

Rodong Sinmun on Songun Politics
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- The Songun politics is now demonstrating its tremendous vitality as a treasured sword for achieving the peace and reunification of the country and its co-prosperity despite the challenges of the separatists at home and abroad. Rodong Sinmun Friday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics serves as an ever-victorious banner for independent reunification as it paves a wide avenue for achieving the reunification of the country, the greatest desire and supreme task of the Korean nation, and a banner of hope because it fully guarantees national prosperity, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics represents a most patriotic option for rejecting outside forces and achieving independent reunification by the concerted efforts of our nation because it has helped foil the foreign forces' moves for aggression and war and defend the cause of national reunification with the might of the matchless and invincible army and placed the national dignity and honor on the highest level. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics backed by the invincible military power serves as a banner instilling immense national pride and self-respect into all Koreans in the north and the south and overseas and propelling the movement for independent reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics of the DPRK strikes the anti-reunification forces inside and outside Korea with terror, but gives strength and encouragement to the pro-reunification patriotic forces at home and abroad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Songun politics has so far fully demonstrated its tremendous vitality as a great banner for achieving independent reunification and national prosperity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The present era of independent reunification is the era in which the movement for it is making progress thanks to the Songun politics. It is the Songun politics that guarantees peace and independent reunification of the country and prosperous future of the nation.

Exploits of Great Persons of Mt. Paektu Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- Ahmad Hassan, general secretary of the Nasser Arab Democratic Party of Egypt, issued a statement on December 16 on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in the statement said that Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the KPA on December 24, 1991 was a historic event of great significance in developing the KPA into an invincible army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the single-minded unity of the whole society has reached the highest level in the DPRK, the statement said that the KPA under the supreme commandership of Kim Jong Il would always demonstrate its might as an invincible army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 December 24 this year marks the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk, the statement said, adding: The most outstanding exploit performed by her in making contributions to the cause of national liberation was that she devotedly defended President Kim Il Sung and brought up Kim Jong Il as the successor to the President and the outstanding leader to carve out the future of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The august name and exploits of Kim Jong Suk will shine long along with eternally prosperous socialist Korea, the statement stressed.

Songun Idea, Songun Politics Studied and Disseminated Worldwide
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 21 (KCNA) -- This year, too, has witnessed brisk worldwide activities to study and disseminate the Songun idea, Songun politics of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il have been brought out in booklet by over 60 political parties, organizations and organs of several countries including the Maritime Territorial Regional Committee of the Communist Party of the Russian Federation, the Workers' Party of Mexico, the Bangladesh-Korea Friendship and Solidarity Committee, the Antri Miek Publishing House of Cambodia and the Publilaser Publishing House of Peru. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Nepalese Association for Supporting the Songun Politics was inaugurated in Nepal with high-ranking officials of the government and political parties attending and organizations for the study of Songun politics were formed in Nigeria and Germany on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A total of more than 600 colorful events including seminars, lectures, reading-sessions and round-table talks took place in over 130 countries and regions including Laos, France, Uganda and Guyana on the occasion of significant holidays of the DPRK. For example, a joint seminar on the Songun idea, Songun politics was held in Abuja, Nigeria, two times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Organizations for the study of the Juche idea and the Songun idea and organizations for friendship and solidarity with the Korean people in more than 70 countries including the Youth Group for the Study of the Juche Idea in Democratic Congo, the British Association for the Study of Songun Politics, the France-Korea Friendship Association and the Brazil-Korea Friendship Association released information bulletins and posted articles on their Internet homepages. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, at least 300 media of the world have widely introduced the essence and originality and invincible might of the Songun idea, Songun politics.

Songun es la gran bandera de la reunificacion y prosperidad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 21 de diciembre (ATCC) -- La politica de Songun (priorizacion militar) exhibe su poderio invencible como remedio para rechazar el desafio de los divisionistas internos y externos y lograr la paz y la reunificacion del pais y la coprosperidad de la nacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el periodico Rodong Sinmun en un articulo individual del dia 21 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La politica de Songun es la bandera invencible de la reunificacion independiente, anhelo y tarea supremos de la nacion, y la bandera de la esperanza que garantiza con firmeza la prosperidad de la nacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este modo politico posibilita frustrar con las fuerzas armadas invencibles las maniobras de agresion y de guerra de las fuerzas foraneas, defender la causa de la reunificacion de la patria y llevar a la altura suprema la dignidad y el orgullo nacionales. Es la bandera patriotica que permite a todos los coreanos rechazar las fuerzas foraneas y lograr la reunificacion independiente con las fuerzas propias de la nacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, esta politica basada en las fuerzas armadas es la bandera estimulante que infunde el gran orgullo y dignidad nacionales a todos los coreanos del Norte, el Sur y en ultramar e impulsa el movimiento por la reunificacion independiente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tambien, da temor a las fuerzas anti-reunificacion internas y externas y deviene fuente de la fuerza y estimulo a las fuerzas patrioticas internas y externas por la reunificacion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el periodo pasado dicha politica manifesto plenamente su inagotable vitalidad como gran bandera de la reunificacion independiente y la prosperidad nacional. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La epoca actual de reunificacion independiente es allanada e impelida por la gran politica de Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Songun garantiza la paz y la reunificacion independiente del pais y la infinita prosperidad futura de la nacion.

Mitin de juramentacion de partido, ejercito y juventud
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, 20 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Tuvo lugar el dia 20 en esta urbe de la provincia de Hamgyong del Norte el mitin del partido, el ejercito y la juventud para rendir el mas sublime homenaje a la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk y jurarle fidelidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la ocasion participaron los cuadros del partido, el ejercito y el Estado, los funcionarios directivos de las instituciones del partido, las fuerzas armadas, organizaciones de masas, ministerios, organos centrales, oficiales y soldados del Ejercito Popular de Corea, funcionarios, trabajadores, jovenes y estudiantes de la provincia y la ciudad mencionadas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@  Ante la estatua de bronce de la heroina fueron depositados un cesto de flores enviado por el Dirigente, el otro de flores en nombre comun del Comite Central y la Comision Militar Central, del PTC, el Comite de Defensa Nacional, el Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema y el Consejo de Ministros, de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, y otros cestos de flores en nombre de unidades del EPC, organos del partido y el Poder, entidades de masas, organismos, empresas, fabricas, granjas y escuelas en la mencionada provincia y ciudad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Todos los participantes rindieron el maximo homenaje a la generala. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al hacer uso de la palabra en representacion del PTC, Choe Thae Bok, miembro suplente del Buro Politico y secretario del CC del PTC, dijo que por su gran vida, sus inmortales hazanas revolucionarias realizadas por la patria, la revolucion, la epoca y la humanidad y sus nobles rasgos de revolucionaria, la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk estara siempre presente en el corazon del pueblo coreano como soldado corps del Presidente Kim Il Sung, destacada activista politica y madre de la revolucion y que la imagen de esta generala del monte Paektu sera eterna en la historia de la Corea del Songun (priorizacion militar). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Subrayo que aun bajo cualesquier vientos y mareas, todos deben apoyar con fidelidad la direccion del Dirigente Kim Jong Il sobre la revolucion mediante el Songun para construir a toda costa una gran potencia prospera socialista en la patria y lograr la victoria final de la causa revolucionaria del Juche, de modo que queden materializados el legado del Presidente y el deseo de Kim Jong Suk en su vida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le siguio en intervenir en representacion del Ejercito Popular de Corea el vicemariscal del EPC Kim Il Chol ministro de las Fuerzas Armadas Populares. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Senalo que la excepcional proeza de Kim Jong Suk registrable en la historia nacional es que dio firme continuidad a la revolucion del Songun al criar al Dirigente Kim Jong Il como lucero del monte Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Continuo que los oficiales y soldados del ejercito popular seran fervientes combatientes y verdaderos companeros de la revolucion del Songun que confian y siguen solo al Comandante Supremo bajo cualesquier circunstancias y comparten hasta el final la vida o muerte con el en el largo camino de la revolucion del Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A nombre de la juventud hablo Ri Yong Chol, primer secretario del CC de la Union de la Juventud Socialista Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La heroina paso toda su grandiosa y noble vida defendiendo a costa de la vida al Presidente Kim Il Sung a quien ella confio absolutamente y dedico todo lo suyo, recordo y prosiguio que ella formo a los jovenes con su noble amor maternal a las nuevas generaciones. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Enfatizo que al aprender la firme concepcion revolucionaria del lider que poseia Kim Jong Suk, todos los jovenes seran primer peloton suicida y heroes de bombas y balas humanas de la epoca del Songun que defienden en lo ideo-politico y con vida al Dirigente y comparten el mismo destino con la Direccion de la Revolucion.

Estudiantes extranjeros publican articulos por el 24 de diciembre
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 21 de diciembre (ATCC) -- Con motivo del 16o aniversario del nombramiento del Dirigente Kim Jong Il como Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea y del 90o aniversario del nacimiento (24 de diciembre) de la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk, los extranjeros que cursan estudios en la Universidad Kim Il Sung y la Universidad Pedagogica Kim Hyong Jik publicaron sus composiciones en un encuentro denominado "Cancion dedicada a diciembre" que tuvo lugar la vispera en el capitalino Club Taedonggang para el Cuerpo Diplomatico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En esta cita iniciada con el coro "Himno al camarada Kim Jong Il" ellos presentaron las piezas preparadas con infinito respeto y veneracion a los Tres Generales del monte Paektu (el Presidente Kim Il Sung, el Dirigente Kim Jong Il y la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El diario "Invencible ejercito", el relato de impresiones "Corea vista con mis ojos", la memoria "Mi primera universidad", la poesia "Madre de Corea", el reportaje sobre la visita "En la Casa Cuna Kim Jong Suk" y otros articulos reflejaron el alma de los estudiantes que veneran infinitamente al Dirigente y anoran mucho a la heroina. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el coro masculino "El General es hijo de la guerrilla", el solo de piano "Kim Jong Suk es nuestra madre", el coro femenino "Arirang repercutido en Jiansanfeng" y otras piezas, ellos elogiaron altamente la noble personalidad del Dirigente y el indoblegable espiritu de lucha y grandes proezas de la heroina.
